20230831105039.description: After two hours of driving on barely paved roads, we rode on this boat for an hour to get to a remote part of the Amazon. The boat driver had this cool New York baseball cap, but he'd never set foot in the city.
20230831105039.label: Boat driver on the Amazon river, wearing a New York baseball cap

20240216153349.description: Even though this city is the skyscraper capital of the world and residents mostly live in dense high rises like these, its housing is still famously expensive. I did a quick hike up Lion Rock to enjoy the view and made friends with some foreign domestic workers doing the same on their day off.
20240216153349.label: From the hike up to Lion Rock, a view of some dense high rises

20240407075152.description: There's only one real city in this country, with many other little towns and villages in the countryside connected via arterial one-lane roads. It took me 10 hours by car to get to this country's western mountainous region, where over a million people live in rural hillside settlements. So many kids would run and yell mzungu when we drove by, but this boy just stared silently, resting on this intricate wooden bicycle.
20240407075152.label: A boy rests on a homemade wooden bicycle

20230917154112.description: As soon as I got to the largest city on the Tibetan Plateau, I was hungry and ready to eat. This Hui man (of the most populous ethnic minority in the region) chopped up some fresh beef for some delicious halal noodle soup.
20230917154112.label: A Hui man chops beef for some delicious noodle soup

20240403114601.description: I have a soft spot for baby elephants, especially seeing them learn to use their trunks. This pair of friends lives in an Instagram-famous African elephant sanctuary, though the hope is that they will one day be released back into the wild.
20240403114601.label: Young elephants cuddling after a playful romp in the mud

20231030091113.description: I took a bus to the top of these mountains in search of high mountain oolong tea, famously produced in this region. These days, authentic gaoshan tea is harder to find, since it's challenging to farm tea trees in these areas where the island often struggles with erosion and landslides.
20231030091113.label: A clear view of mountainous farms and towns

20230905214846.description: Though this looks like a desert, it actually receives a lot of rainso much that lagoons form during the rainy season. After spending two days trekking 25 kilometers through the sand, I concluded that this is perhaps the most beautiful place I've seen. My guide told me that only gringos are crazy enough to do the trek, which involves starting off at 2:30 am to beat the midday heat.
20230905214846.label: People trek through sand dunes and lagoons

20240423170649.description: Steps away from this view is the Al-Balad neighborhood, filled with centuries-old coral-brick buildings undergoing a multi-billion dollar restoration effort as the country attracts more foreign sightseers. This city has always accommodated pilgrims visiting the holy city of Makkah, but it was closed off from international tourism until late 2019.
20240423170649.label: Palm trees surround a white mosque by the water

20240403070440.description: Seeing big game during a savannah safari is an amazing experience because the animals can be spotted from miles away. In this case, these giraffes were easy to spotthey greeted us as soon as we entered this national park, conveniently located within the city limits of the capital.
20240403070440.label: Giraffes stand tall above the savannah

20211016181712.description: This national park is named after its iconic trees, which the area's original settlers thought resembled a Biblical figure walking with hands outstretched. I loved wandering aimlessly in the backcountry, getting lost among what felt like recurrent landmarks, then setting up camp for the night and admiring this sunset.
20211016181712.label: Characteristically bent and prickly trees dot the landscape in front of a pink sunset

20220501182106.description: I first saw this mural on an empty building near this city's central train station, and I was struck by the boldness of its message in a city once divided by a wall during the Cold War. Since then, though, it looks like its pleas have gone unanswered. The last time I visited this city it had already been painted over.
20220501182106.label: An iconic mural that reads STOP WARS

20230908155353.description: This gorgeous view is (literally) worth its cost. To get to the trailhead for this hike, we took a minibus up through the heart of Vidigal, one of this city's famous favelas. Though the hike is supposed to be open to the public, it was guarded by a man with a rifle who demanded we pay a small fee each to enter.
20230908155353.label: Views of a beautiful beachside city

20231113203843.description: A few blocks away from the world's busiest pedestrian crossing is this much calmer listening bar. Using a top tier sound system, the DJ plays records from a variety of genres, perfect for enjoying over some delicious cocktails.
20231113203843.label: A DJ plays a record in front of a well-stocked bar

20210228094956.description: This marine preserve is one of the best snorkeling spots I've been to, enclosed in a bay easily seen from the top of a nearby abandoned WWII railway track. While snorkeling here, I was amazed by the sight of a little octupus swimming near the shore, and I saw plenty humuhumunukunukuapua'a, a type of triggerfish known to be aggressive towards swimmers.
20210228094956.label: A view of a tropical bay famous for its snorkeling

20240101000443.description: I'm not usually impressed by fireworks displays, but this one deserved some recognition. For a few glorious minutes, various lights and colors shot off the tiers of what was formerly the tallest building in the world. I watched the show as revelers around me sat quietly on picnic blankets.
20240101000443.label: Fireworks shoot off the tiers of a skyscraper

20231228120001.description: On the drive from this capital city airport, President El-Sisi shows off his relationships with powerful friends--Xi Jinping in this photo, and Vladimir Putin in another one.
20231228120001.label: President El-Sisi shakes hands with President Xi Jinping in this portrait near the airport

20240319114925.description: At the grave of Ludwig Boltzmann, his equation for entropy is the sole inscription above his bust. He and another physicist born in the same city, Erwin Schrdinger, were some of the first scientists to theorize on how biological organisms struggle against their inevitable increase in entropy. At some philosophical level, it's a good reminder for me that we exist to make something meaningful out of the chaos of this universe.
20240319114925.label: The headstone of Ludwig Boltzmann highlights his formulation for statistical entropy

20240416124540.description: This tropical island has always held a strategic position within Indian Ocean trade routes. Fishermen maintain local wooden boats, called dhows, in the same way they've done for millennia. Here, they're burning leaves underneath the boards to clear off any algae and pests. Afterwards, they'll reapply a layer of coconut rope for waterproofing.
20240416124540.label: Leaves burn underneath a traditional wooden boat

20240323134848.description: I joined a group of hikers on a 12-kilometer trek through tea fields around an hour out from the city. Today, this country is one of the world's largest tea exporters, a lingering effect from a complicated colonial history. As one of my new friends put it, the British drink so much tea, but what tea farms do you see on their own land?
20240323134848.label: A group of hikers navigates between rows of tea trees on a tea farm

20220709011654.description: This club's bottle service came with a nerdy message: the first few digits of pi. It's an MIT tradition to host a class reunion on the 3.14th year anniversary of graduation every year in this nightlife destination. It felt surreal to run into the same classmates I used to run into down the Infinite on the Strip instead.
20220709011654.label: Big signs for the digits of pi are held up in a nightclub

20230916162523.description: Photos of this city usually are from the Bund, where classical European-style buildings sit across the river from towering skyscrapers. Instead, I ventured further out into the city for a more peaceful view and enjoyed this newer green space along the waterfront.
20230916162523.label: Overlooking a park with a distant city skyline

20211002062526.description: It's easy to come to this beautiful seaside nation and stay only along the coast. Its barrier reef is part of the largest reef system in the western hemisphere, and I spent two weeks there on my first solo trip learning to scuba dive. I also went inland, though, traveling to a jungle town to see its Mayan ruins and underground caves. Near the bus stop, I spotted this stray dog patiently waiting for a meat shop to open its doors.
20211002062526.label: A stray dog waits for a meat shop to open

20240213150531.description: In many places I've traveled to, it's a common sight to see neighborhood men sitting around outside the shops, chatting and killing time. This spot in my grandparents' small town was the first place I'd seen a group of women doing the same.
20240213150531.label: Women sit around on little stools outside a local shop

20240224175720.description: You don't always need to travel far to see new sights. My favorite local park is a lovely place to relax on a sunny weekend day, with beautiful views of old Victorian houses and the downtown city skyline. It's always filled with interesting characters, like this man with a T-Rex costume who terrified my friend's pup. After the sun sets, I like to head over a few blocks over and grab a bite to eat from any of the nearby taqueras.
20240224175720.label: A dog stares down a man wearing a T-rex costume

20231222154735.description: The rest of this resort town was super clean and organized, with wide roads and a desert-like Las Vegas feel. In contrast, this cliffside lounge had a distinctly bohemian vibe, blending Bedouin and ancient decor alongside random old trinkets. After a long day scuba diving on the Rea Sea, it was a perfect place to unwind.
20231222154735.label: A cliffside lounge perfect for enjoying a sunset shisha

20230527105911.description: I visited this alligator ranch in the U.S. state that inspired the scientific name of these prehistoric creatures. In a catastrophic hurricane in 2005, the swamp waters rose around 15 feet, overflowing so high that many alligators escaped.
20230527105911.label: Sleepy alligators rest among green swamp waters

20231209143137.description: Our original plan was to hike up this famously flat-topped mountain, then take the cable car down. At the top, we walked across the mountain for kilometers to reach the cable car station, only to realize it was closed due to high winds. Instead, I found myself hiking down scared I'd get blown off my feet.
20231209143137.label: Hiking down from a flat-topped mountain on a windy day

20230208210524.description: This shelf in the White House Press Briefing Room is visible only from the back, and it's filled with little figurines and souvenirs from journalists who've spent time there.
20230208210524.label: A hidden shelf in the White House Briefing Room filled with memorabilia from the various journalists who've spent time there

20231129001001.description: This township's claim to fame is a street that was home to two Nobel Laureates (Nelson Mandela and Desmond Tutu). Instead of a historical tour, I joined a group going to a weekly Tuesday night music jam, where the crowd enthusiastically replied music jam! whenever a performer prompted us with sawuboma. I heard some really amazing live music, but unfortunately many performers didn't have recordings online of their work.
20231129001001.label: Musicians perform some of the best live music I've heard in an intimate venue

20220328115607.description: The center of this ancient city, one of the world's oldest, is divided into four quarters and is a holy site for the three major Abrahamic religions. It's had a complicated past, surviving countless wars and sieges, and when I visited I felt a sense of tense coexistence. Steps away from the church containing Jesus' tomb, shops line the streets where tourists can buy all sorts of colorful wares.
20220328115607.label: Shops selling colorful goods along a street market

20240126173323.description: I saw this boy riding an adult bicycle as I sat on the back of a scooter, whizzing through local streets. In the background, flags fly for various political parties ahead of the February 2024 national election, though this province is the only one in the country run by a sultan rather than an elected governor.
20240126173323.label: A boy stands with an oversized bicycle

20230923165405.description: These towering sand dunes in the Kumtag Desert are at risk of engulfing their neighboring ancient Silk Road city. Tour operators run a lucrative business here, managing hordes of camels to take tourists up to a picturesque oasis near the edge of the desert. Traveling around this country, I found that there were countless fascinating sights, but assembly-line tourism like this camel ride factory spoiled the experience of visiting.
20230923165405.label: Camels line up to take tourists up towering sand dunes

20220424175205.description: One of my favorite European cities is known for its numerous historic canals and cycling paths. Bridges spanning the canals are a popular place to park your bike, a necessary space in a city where there are more bicycles than inhabitants. Unfortunately, many abandoned bikes end up littering the canals, and I've always wondered how often people fall in as well!
20220424175205.label: Bicycles are parked along a bridge spanning a canal

20231210111331.description: This city at the southern tip of the continent is the most Californian place I've been to outside of California. It has similar laid back vibes, gentrified neighborhoods, trendy cafes and restaurants, and beautiful mountains and beaches. One of its big differences is an introduced love for rugbythis man was raving about how he planned to streak across the field at the nearby rugby sevens championships.
20231210111331.label: A man stands proudly painted with his home rugby team's flag across his body

20240204143516.description: This cave complex hosts a century-old Hindu temple in a country known for its diverse ethnic groups (with sometimes complicated relations). The steps leading up to the main shrine were controversially painted rainbow colors in 2018 without permission and now offer a lively Instagram photo backdrop.
20240204143516.label: Colorful steps adorn a mountainside Hindu temple

20240310134208.description: I heard from many Europeans that their chief winter activity was skiing, and this town was a great place to hit the slopes of the Alps. Though I didn't visit for the snow, I stopped for a bite to eat at a trendy cafe. To get us seated, I offered to share a table with another woman on her own, and we ended up chatting for hours (and had a surprising amount in common!).
20240310134208.label: Colorful buildings stand in front of snow-capped mountains

20210515153742.description: This famous city park has many little attractions to explore, including this lake. A friend and I walked up its length as part of a longer day hike from Battery Park to the Bronx (almost 20 miles total!).
20210515153742.label: A lake in the midst of a famous city park offers a reprieve from its chaos

20231113164005.description: People know this country for its capital, the most populous city in the world, but its other destinations are often overlooked. This smaller seaside town was only an hour and a half train ride from the city, and locals love to come here to surf in the summer. These ladies had a different idea, though, and opted to explore the town by rickshaw.
20231113164005.label: A friendly rickshaw driver and his passengers all wave at the photographer

20240420135355.description: These minibuses are a popular and mostly reliable form of transport in cities without dedicated transit infrastructure. Conductors usher in passengers until the bus is full, often stretching the definition of full. On one bus, it was so crowded I could only stand on one foot! Orthodox Christian prints hang above the driver in every bus, a lasting influence in a region once home to one of the world's oldest Christian kingdoms.
20240420135355.label: Cramped in a public bus with a view of Orthodox Christian art

20231023135233.description: I can't really read written Chinese, but as I cycled past this sign on a two-week ride around this independent island territory, I guessed that Kiss and Ride wasn't a literal translation. After dismounting the bike for the day, I translated this picture, sure enough, the original text just reads Pick up and drop off area. I found this quirky sign delightful in a place where public displays of affection are uncommon.
20231023135233.label: A train station sign that reads Kiss and Ride in English but something different in Chinese

20220326123953.description: Like many other European cities, this city has an enviably extensive metro system. What makes it better than most is its extensive artworkit's been nicknamed the world's longest art gallery. Being underground was also a great way to escape the cold when I visited in the winter.
20220326123953.label: A blue mural painted into the rock ceiling of a metro station

20240122035644.description: This country has the world's largest number of active volcanoes, reflected in its over 17,000 islands. I certainly didn't have time to visit them all, but my favorite experience was this midnight hike up to the top of this volcano and its active sulfur mining site. We arrived just before dawn, the perfect time to see its famous blue flames shoot up from its acidic gas vents.
20240122035644.label: Blue fire erupts from a volcano popular for sulfur mining

20240314174914.description: Under the pilberk Castle in the middle of this city, this nuclear bunker in a former Soviet satellite state is now a museum and hostel. I stayed here for one night, and that was enough for me! In the event of nuclear war, heating and internet access are low on the list of priorities.
20240314174914.label: A room in a former nuclear bunker, now converted to a hostel

20240112172556.description: This majority Muslim island is lesser known than its trendy, Instagrammable Hindu neighbor. Motorized scooters are a popular way to get around, and on an hour long ride back from waterfalls on the island's northern side, we rode behind a family with cute baby. As the ride progressed, the baby impressively fell asleep while his dad zoomed in and out of traffic.
20240112172556.label: A mother holds her sleepy baby on the back of a scooter

20240208150420.description: Though this city has the oldest European colonial presence in Asia, these buildings aren't direct evidence of its influence. Instead, casinos develop elaborate replicas to entice attraction-seeking gamblers and shoppers. Next to where I took this photo, visitors posed for photos inside a London-style double decker bus.
20240208150420.label: European-style architecture alongside an Eiffel Tower replica

20240423142416.description: Women were only allowed to drive here in 2019, and I used my visit here as an opportunity to exercise that right. I drove an hour out of the city to visit this shipwreck and left my car to explore without anyone in sight. When I returned, border police were waiting for me. Their English was so choppy they couldn't ask for my passport, but they were incredibly friendly and helped me take some pictures.
20240423142416.label: A shipwreck off the shore of the Red Sea

20231117200958.description: I love a good bowl of northern-style pho. The best spot in this city isn't in a streetside restaurant but actually involves going through a tight alleyway, up stairs, then into a woman's living room where she serves you fresh, warm bowls of noodle soup.
20231117200958.label: Household shrine at a family-run ph restaurant

20231226165146.description: People were amazed to hear that I walked from Tahrir Square to Khan el-Khalili, and this scene captures why: traveling by foot in this city involves all kinds of challenges. Adding to the absurdity, the building in the background was left half demolished, with a face but no body.
20231226165146.label: Man jumps over pedestrian barrier with half demolished building in background

20220703140600.description: To escape this city's summer heat, we went to this famous public pool to cool down, only to find that it had paid admission. Instead, we swam for free at these springs downstream, alongside tons of other people (and dogs).
20220703140600.label: Swimmers at the local watering hole

20240218132352.description: In this moving sculpture, realistic figures of geriatric world leaders sit on motorized wheelchairs. They drive around aimlessly, bumping into each other and sometimes getting entangled. I was surprised at the cultural and political candor of artwork in this museum, given the recent national security crackdown amid a rocky transition from British to Chinese rule.
20240218132352.label: Life-like sculptures of geriatric world leaders aimlessly bump into each other on motorized wheelchairs

20240118130627.description: This South Asian island is a popular destination, both for backpackers and honeymooners. I heard from many people that these parts were much sleepier before the pandemic, but when I was there the touristic feel was obvious. Still, I enjoyed this visit to a busy monkey sanctuary, where a thousand macaques roam free. These curious critters inspected my feet as I walked by.
20240118130627.label: Curious monkeys inspect my feet

20231221185444.description: Dner kebab can be found all over Europe, but it's best to go to its source where this vertical rotisserie was first invented. This dog waiting outside the shop had the right idea, though I didn't stay around long enough to see if she accomplished anything with her begging.
20231221185444.label: A dog looks longingly into a kebab shop at night

20240406102231.description: There are about 1,000 mountain gorillas left in the world, and half of them are found in this national park. With a permit, visitors can join park rangers as they track the locations of each gorilla family every day, rain or shine, at times venturing deep into the jungle. The recognition was obviousthis silverback watched us very closely, and a mother gorilla made prolonged eye contact with me as her baby played on her back.
20240406102231.label: A silverback mountain gorilla stares straight at the camera

20240429123736.description: In this country's most populous city, the world's largest open air laundry handles one lakh (100,000) clothes a day from homes, hotels, and laundromats. It's also a tourist attractionone man made the mistake of buying a souvenir from one of the peddlers and found himself crowded by other merchants trying to make a similar sale. They followed him all to the way to his car, banging on his window as he closed the door!
20240429123736.label: An overhead view of the world's largest open air laundry
